tripleo_ansible/roles/tripleo_etcd/templ.message:
The conditional will result on the 'wal-dir' setting being excluded from the file unless a non-zero length value is defined. This is different than what's shown in etcd.conf.yaml.sample, which lists the setting but with a blank value.

Is it OK to exclude the setting entirely? Alternatively, you do replicate the sample file using an 'else' clause, like this:

{% if tripleo_etcd_wal_dir is defined and tripleo_etcd_wal_dir|length %}
# Path to the dedicated wal directory.
wal-dir: "{{ tripleo_etcd_wal_dir }}"
{% else %}
wal-dir:
{% endif %}

UPDATE: [1] shows an empty string, so maybe tripleo_etcd_wal_dir can have a '' default value, and you could eliminate the j2 conditional.

[1] https://etcd.io/docs/v3.5/op-guide/configuration/

